        {
            "_id": "czJ9UzjCu5FvJvDI",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Bastard's Shame",
            "sort": 900000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Velicarn harbors deep feelings of shame and anger about his heritage, and a PC can capitalize on this to insult him or to distract him as follows.</p>\n<p><strong>Insult Velicarn</strong> The PC attempts a DC 30 Intimidation check to [[/act demoralize dc=30 options=inflicts:slowed]] Velicarn. On a critical success, he's also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} by his anger for 1 round. If he's also already @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] as a result of being distracted, he takes @Damage[6d6[mental]] damage (@Check[will|dc:30|basic] save) on a success (@Damage[12d6[mental]] damage on a critical success).</p>\n<p><strong>Distract Velicarn</strong> The PC attempts a DC 28 Deception check to [[/act feint dc=28 options=inflicts:slowed]] Velicarn. On a critical success, he's also slowed 1 by his anger for 1 round. If he's also already slowed as a result of being insulted, he takes @Damage[6d6[mental]] damage (@Check[will|dc:30|basic] save) on a success (@Damage[12d6[mental]] damage on a critical success).</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "xElxJeroNz5kn0Y6",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Board Soul",
            "sort": 1000000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "reaction"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> Velicarn reduces a creature to 0 HP with void damage</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Fragments of the creature's soul, manifesting as a vaguely spectral image of the creature, are pulled into the carriage and thereafter seen within, hammering silently on the windows while screaming to be rescued. A creature that dies while a fragment of its soul is trapped within the carriage can't become undead or be brought back to life until Velicarn is destroyed. A creature that's rescued before death is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} as long as part of its soul remains aboard the Black Coach.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "death",
                        "divine"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "5aRA8keG76255FAe",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Coin's Return",
            "sort": 1100000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A PC can toss @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Velicarn's Cursed Coin], or the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Fortune's Coin] it becomes after it's uncursed, at the death coach as an Interact action whenever Velicarn is within 30 feet. Doing so causes the coin to vanish in a sudden flash. The coin is destroyed, and Velicarn must attempt a @Check[will|dc:35|options:damaging-effect,inflicts:off-guard,inflicts:stunned] save (@Check[will|dc:37|options:damaging-effect,inflicts:off-guard,inflicts:stunned] if the coin is no longer cursed) with the following results.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Velicarn is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] until the start of his turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Velicarn takes @Damage[5d6[spirit]] damage and is off-guard until the start of his turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> Velicarn takes @Damage[10d6[spirit]] damage, is off-guard until the end of the PC's next turn, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Velicarn takes @Damage[20d6[spirit]] damage, is off-guard for 1 minute, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 3}.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "1OjGOmq2f6DTwLSj",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Discorporation",
            "sort": 1200000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "deathNote": true,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>If Velicarn is reduced to 0 Hit Points, the Black Coach and the two fiendish horses that drive it vanish immediately, and Velicarn transforms into a dullahan armed with a +2 greater striking astral battle axe. He falls @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Prone] in a space of his choice previously occupied by the death coach and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round. As soon as he ends a round without the slowed condition, he transforms back into a death coach and regains @Damage[100[healing]] Hit Points. Only by destroying him in his dullahan form before this (typically 2 rounds, unless his slowed condition is extended) can he be truly put to rest.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
